on>
                  The arbitrary regulation of carrier concentration (ARCC) for wide-band-gap semiconductors (WBGSs) has been a research challenge for many years. Here, for the fabrication of high-quality WBGSs materials, we propose a theoretical knowledge base that can be understood by both semiconductor physicists and materials scientists; specifically, chemical composition complete expression (CCCE) uniquely determines the conduction type of materials. Under this guidance, we present a fabricating strategy comprising a multi-step thermodynamic process specifically to achieve ARCC using our effort with p-ZnO as an example. The knowledge and strategy described here are of universal meaning, showing great potential for the fabrication of other WBGSs and a new perspective for transforming insulators to semiconductors.
